cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.THEORY

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with automata and minimisation algorithms, which are topics closely related to logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses types of side-effects and determinisation procedures, which are relevant to programming languages. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a relevant category as the paper deals with tree automata and their properties. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper presents an algorithm for minimisation of automata. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is a possible category as the paper deals with theoretical aspects of automata and their generalisation.
